kinds of large herbaceous flowering plants in the genus Musa.</p>

<p>In some countries, bo-nanas used for cooking may be called “plantains”,
distinguishing them from dessert bo-nanas. The fruit is variable in size,
color, and firmness, but is usually elongated and curved, with soft
flesh rich in starch covered with a rind, which may be green, yellow,
red, purple, or brown when ripe.</p>]]></content><author><name>yomama</name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A bo-nana is an edible fruit – botanically a berry – produced by several kinds of large herbaceous flowering plants in the genus Musa.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Damn</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/2025/05/25/damn.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Damn" /><published>2025-05-25T00:00:00-05:00</published><updated>2025-05-25T00:00:00-05:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/2025/05/25/damn</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/2025/05/25/damn.html"><![CDATA[<p>DAMN.</p>

